@import org.operaton.dev.starter.templates.model.ProjectConfig
@import org.operaton.dev.starter.templates.model.ProjectType
@import org.operaton.dev.starter.templates.model.BuildSystem
@param ProjectConfig config
!{var isMaven = config.buildSystem() == BuildSystem.MAVEN;}
!{var isGradleGroovy = config.buildSystem() == BuildSystem.GRADLE_GROOVY;}
!{var isProcessApp = config.projectType() == ProjectType.PROCESS_APPLICATION;}
!{var isDockerCompose = config.dockerCompose();}
!{var runCmd = isMaven ? "./mvnw spring-boot:run" : "./gradlew bootRun";}
!{var buildCmd = isMaven ? "./mvnw verify" : "./gradlew build";}
!{var wrapperScript = isMaven ? "mvnw" : "gradlew";}
# ${config.projectName()}

An Operaton BPM project generated by [Operaton Starter](https://start.operaton.org).

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- Java ${config.javaVersion()}+

The ${isMaven ? "Maven" : "Gradle"} wrapper is bundled — no separate build tool installation required.
@if(isDockerCompose)
- Docker (for Docker Compose)
@endif

### First-Time Setup (Unix / macOS)

The wrapper script is not executable after ZIP extraction. Run this once before your first build:

```bash
chmod +x ./${wrapperScript}
```

Windows users: use `.\\${wrapperScript}${isMaven ? ".cmd" : ".bat"}` — no extra setup needed.

### Build and Run

```bash
${buildCmd}
```

@if(isProcessApp)
Start the application:

```bash
${runCmd}
```

@if(isDockerCompose)
Alternatively, start with `docker-compose`:
```bash
docker-compose up --build
```
@endif

The Operaton Cockpit is available at: http://localhost:${config.serverPort()}/operaton

On first start you will be asked to set up an admin user account.
@endif

## What to Do Next

1. **Explore the BPMN process** — open `src/main/resources/${config.artifactId()}.bpmn` in [Operaton Cockpit](http://localhost:${config.serverPort()}/operaton)
   or an Operaton compatible modeling tool (e.g. [Flowset Studio](https://plugins.jetbrains.com/plugin/25655-flowset--bpm-studio/)
   or [Camunda Modeler](https://downloads.camunda.cloud/release/camunda-modeler/))
@if(isProcessApp)
2. **Implement your logic** — replace the stub in `SkeletonDelegate.java` with your business logic
3. **Run the integration test** — `ProcessIT.java` deploys and executes the skeleton process end-to-end
@else
2. **Deploy the archive** — build and deploy the ${config.deploymentTarget().map(t -> t.name().toLowerCase().replace('_', ' ')).orElse("archive")} to your Operaton engine
@endif
4. **Read the docs** — [Operaton Documentation](https://docs.operaton.org/docs/documentation/)

## Troubleshooting

**Port ${config.serverPort()} already in use**
Change the port in `application.properties`: `server.port=8123` (or any free port) and restart the application.

**H2 datasource not configured**
The default configuration uses H2 in-memory. For persistent storage, replace the `spring.datasource.*` properties with your database settings.

**Java version mismatch**
Ensure your runtime Java version matches the compiler target (`java.version=${config.javaVersion()}`).
Check with `java -version`.
